-m-right" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1661271093437"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center gf-elm-center-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-family: Roboto; font-size: 16px; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(94, 94, 94);">So how do you apply or use mindfulness?&nbsp;</p><p style="font-family: Roboto; font-size: 16px; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(94, 94, 94);"><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.025em; text-align: inherit;">Below is a helpful step by step description of how to use mindful meditation,&nbsp;</span></p><p style="font-family: Roboto; font-size: 16px; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(94, 94, 94);"><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.025em; text-align: inherit;">with information from an article by Harvard staff writer Liz Mineo.&nbsp;</span></p><p style="font-family: Roboto; font-size: 16px; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(94, 94, 94);"><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.025em; text-align: inherit;">Mindful Meditation Made Easy¹³</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1661270825282" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-20 gf_gs-spacing-md-m-top gf_gs-spacing-sm-p-left gf_gs-spacing-sm-p-right" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1661270825282" data-extraclass="" data-row-gap="20px" data-layout-lg="12" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1660936798945" data-id="1660936798945"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1661270825304" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1661270825304" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-